{
  "texts": [
    "Even though Reaxys performs better on average, some of the molecules correctly found in PatCID are not found in Reaxys.",
    "Even restricting the evaluation to documents annotated in Reaxys, PatCID covers 8.7% of molecules from D2C-RND and 5.5% of molecules from D2C-UNI, which are not covered in Reaxys.",
    "To complement this analysis, a comparison of the number of molecules annotated patent in PatCID and Reaxys for the random (D2C-RND) benchmark is shown in Supplementary Fig. 5.",
    "PatCID bridges the gap between automatically-and manuallycreated databases, and stands out as a complementary tool to manually-curated databases.",
    "Patent documents in the field of organic chemistry are typically written following two different styles."
  ]
}